%S A119471 1,1,1,4,8,17,50,146,399,1087,3042,8741,25509,75259,223529,665215,
%T A119471 1983226,5931158,17800505,53627756,162206221,492399027,1499501067,
%U A119471 4579193127,14017819056,43001141630,132154209754,406818719006,1254224223578,3872184906554,11970390368001,37051341871259
%N A119471 G.f. A(x) equals the limit of the composition of functions F_n(x) = (x + x^n) starting with F_1(x) = x and repeating F_{n+1}(x) = F_n(x) + F_n(x)^(n+1). Thus, A(x) = ... o (x + x^n) o ... o (x + x^3) o (x + x^2) o x, where operator 'o' denotes composition.
%C A119471 Conjecture: the radius of convergence r satisfies A(r) = 1, where r = 0.3104429499 8756901289 5410716645 4712860635 3102024283 5871760958 3347115394 2327073684 7... Equivalently, if we set y = r and repeat y = y + y^n as n = 2,3,4,..., the process yields y = 1 as a limit.
%H A119471 Paul D. Hanna, <a href="/A119471/b119471.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1975</a>
%e A119471 G.f.: A(x) = x + x^2 + x^3 + 4*x^4 + 8*x^5 + 17*x^6 + 50*x^7 + 146*x^8 + 399*x^9 + 1087*x^10 + 3042*x^11 + 8741*x^12 + ...
%e A119471 A(x) is the limit of the composition of functions F_n(x) = (x + x^n), starting with F_1(x) = x and repeating F_{n+1}(x) = (x + x^(n+1)) o F_n(x) as illustrated below.
%e A119471 F_2(x) = (x + x^2) o x;
%e A119471 F_3(x) = (x + x^3) o (x + x^2) o x = x + x^2 + x^3 + 3*x^4 + 3*x^5 + x^6;
%e A119471 F_4(x) = (x + x^4) o F_3(x) = x + x^2 + x^3 + 4*x^4 + 7*x^5 + 11*x^6 + ...
%e A119471 F_5(x) = (x + x^5) o F_4(x) = x + x^2 + x^3 + 4*x^4 + 8*x^5 + 16*x^6 + ...
%e A119471 F_6(x) = (x + x^6) o F_5(x) = x + x^2 + x^3 + 4*x^4 + 8*x^5 + 17*x^6 + ...
%e A119471 F_7(x) = (x + x^7) o (x + x^6) o (x + x^5) o (x + x^4) o (x + x^3) o (x + x^2) o x = x + x^2 + x^3 + 4*x^4 + 8*x^5 + 17*x^6 + 50*x^7 + 145*x^8 + ...
%e A119471 etc.
%e A119471 SPECIFIC VALUES.
%e A119471 A(t) = 1/2 at t = 0.288559191494800993203731731121982468098429942673212120699...;
%e A119471   set y = t and repeat y = y + y^n as n = 2,3,4,... yields y = 1/2 as a limit.
%e A119471 A(t) = 2/5 at t = 0.26211206260215595456102382659148425321601535608074...
%e A119471 A(t) = 1/3 at t = 0.23648395533456266035083329395729431731120023685058...
%e A119471 A(t) = 1/4 at t = 0.19465116797744952166351583836381098310239167766184...
%e A119471 A(t) = 1/5 at t = 0.16414379034361087964647775235426196880343105426409...
%e A119471 A(2/7) = 0.48627618277358163879863010073510184673891142475353...
%e A119471   set y = 2/7 and repeat y = y + y^n as n = 2,3,4,... yields y = A(2/7) as a limit.
%e A119471 A(1/4) = 0.36629298970934721419002882309226036579441425669523...
%e A119471 A(1/5) = 0.25952689303552916018870638690456573933139342060811...
%e A119471 A(1/6) = 0.20389303523340129652448502349743472476382872440444...
%o A119471 (PARI) {a(n) = my(F=x); for(k=2, n, F = subst(x + x^k, x, F +x*O(x^n)); ); polcoef(GF=F, n)}
%o A119471 {upto(n) = a(n); Vec(GF)}
